  <mads:note type="source">"Blandus Rube'llius, whose grandfather was only a Roman knight of Tibur,
      married in A.D. 33 Julia, the daughter of Drusus, the son of the emperor Tiberius, whence
      Blandus is called the progener of Tiberius...." from Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography
      and Mythology, Vol 3 1870, p. 492.</mads:note>
  
